One of my patients sent me this video from @jillianmichaels about the new drug semaglutide. She has a gross misunderstanding of obesity and why people fail to lose weight along with how these trials are run.

I forgot to add in a quick segment about the fear of thyroid cancer. It is a very rare type of thyroid cancer that rats are predisposed to. There is no signal that this occurs in humans.

I have many patients on this medicine who finally feel they have a normal appetite. It’s not that they lack willpower, it’s because it’s physiology! Let me know what you think of the video.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Dr. Spencer Nadolsky on July 26, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of one or more people and text that says 'Dr. Spencer Nadolsky @DrNadolsky Even IF we find the perfect diet for each person using DNA, microbiome, glucose monitors, and other biomarkers, we still have the issue issue of getting people to stick to it. That ain't happening anytime soon.'.

node.text:
All of these efforts to personalize nutrition based on various things like dna and microbiome are fun to study. The issue is even if there is some diet that matches exactly what we are to eat on an individual level for health purposes, most people wouldn’t follow it anyway.

Findings ways to help people adhere to dietary patterns desperately needs to be studied more.

A few people mentioned that the perfect diet is the one you can stick to. A lot of my patients can stick to a diet full of pizza, French fries, and regular soda. 😂❤️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Dr. Spencer Nadolsky on July 25, 2021. May be a cartoon of text that says 'Probability of contagion Very High @DrNadolsky High Still High want to Hey do be and sell Herbalife? business you owner None'.

node.text: This is still funny a year later. I used to get duped into these MLM meetings all of the time. Now I can tell from a mile away! 😂❤️😂

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Dr. Spencer Nadolsky on July 24, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Dr. Spencer Nadolsky @DrNadolsky Being "on" or "off" a diet is silly. You didn't get 100% or 0% in grade school. There were many grades in between.'.

node.text:
Good reminder on the weekend. You can of course deviate from your usual weekday eating. Understand it’s all energy balance for weight (with fluid shift fluctuations).

Get out of the all or nothing diet mindset!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Dr. Spencer Nadolsky on July 23, 2021. May be an image of fire, outdoors and text that says 'YOU TRYING TO GET HEALTHIER 5 HOURS OF SLEEP POOR DIET LITTLE PHYSICAL ACTIVITY @DrNadolsky imgflip.com GREENS DRINK'.

node.text:
Many people “major in the minors”. They focus on things that will make the smallest impact on whatever they are trying to achieve.

In this example, I picked greens drinks. People are always drinking these things when their diet, physical activity, and sleep are overall not that great. You could insert any supplement here really.

In case anyone asks, I’m not a fan of these drinks regardless. These companies try to pack a large amount of antioxidants and all sorts of things into a concentrated powder. There are some concerns with getting such unnaturally high boluses of various antioxidants at once.

Obviously if you need 1500 calories, the amount of carbs you can eat while still getting enough protein and fat will be limited, but it’s all relative.

node.text:
Just a reminder!

Carbohydrates are not inherently fattening. This has been studied over and over again. It’s true that highly refined ultra processed foods containing carbohydrates (and fat) are easily over eaten. But carbs come in different packages. Think strawberries. Think legumes. Don’t think donuts snd cookies, which aren’t satiating and also contain fat (high calorie).

I’ve talked about artificial sweeteners many times before. They are also not fattening. Anyone who says this doesn’t have a clue.

Fasting helps people lose weight because they eat less. They literally aren’t eating. The proposed magic from fasting for weight loss doesn’t exist.

Detox drinks are stupid. Not much else needed to say.

When it comes to diet success, the most important aspect is adherence or how consistent they are with the dietary recommendations (as long as those recommendations follow the principles of energy balance - calories in vs out). Trying to be perfect may lead to complete burnout and quitting. Instead shoot for 80-90% and you’ll be fine. ❤️
